1561d5c3-0189-1000-b9fc-4d82acd70c97.jpeg', '2023-07-02 13:54:40.613029', '2');
INSERT INTO public.tbl_exams ( category_id, category_name, created_at, created_by, description, download_number, exam_duration, exam_name, exam_type, owner_id, thumbnail, updated_at, updated_by) VALUES ( 6, 'Amazon Web Service', '2023-07-02 15:21:24.634645', '2', 'AWS Cloud Essentials is a comprehensive training and certification program designed to provide learners with a foundational understanding of Amazon Web Services (AWS) and its cloud computing services. This program covers a wide range of topics related to AWS, including the basics of cloud computing, AWS architectural principles, essential AWS services, security, and compliance in the AWS Cloud. Through practical exercises and hands-on learning, learners gain valuable insights into AWS core services like Amazon EC2, Amazon S3, and Amazon RDS. They also learn about pricing models, AWS support options, and best practices for building and deploying applications on AWS. The AWS Cloud Essentials program helps learners understand the benefits and advantages of using AWS for their businesses, such as scalability, elasticity, and cost-effectiveness. It equips them with the knowledge to make informed decisions regarding AWS services and solutions. By completing the program and obtaining the AWS Cloud Essentials certification, learners demonstrate their understanding of fundamental AWS concepts and their ability to leverage AWS services to drive business value. The AWS Cloud Essentials program serves as an essential starting point for individuals and organizations embarking on their cloud computing journey with AWS, providing a solid foundation for further exploration and specialization within the AWS ecosystem.', 0, 60, 'AWS Cloud Essentials Quiz with W3School', 'FREE', 2, 'http://localhost:8763/api/v1/files/images/exams/15b13e10-0189-1000-a34f-5d7a6c1d0c6e.jpg', '2023-07-02 15:21:24.634645', '2');
INSERT INTO public.tbl_exams ( category_id, category_name, created_at, created_by, description, download_number, exam_duration, exam_name, exam_type, owner_id, thumbnail, updated_at, updated_by) VALUES ( 6, 'Amazon Web Service', '2023-07-02 16:00:09.472808', '2', 'AWS Serverless is a paradigm and set of services provided by Amazon Web Services (AWS) that allows developers to build and deploy applications without having to provision or manage servers. With AWS Serverless, developers can focus on writing code and creating business logic while AWS handles the infrastructure management. The key component of AWS Serverless is AWS Lambda, a serverless compute service that allows developers to run their code in response to events, such as changes in data, user actions, or system events. Lambda automatically scales and provisions resources based on the incoming request load, ensuring optimal performance and cost-efficiency. In addition to Lambda, AWS Serverless also includes other services such as Amazon API Gateway for building and managing APIs, AWS Step Functions for orchestrating serverless workflows, and AWS DynamoDB for serverless database storage. The serverless architecture provides benefits such as reduced operational overhead, pay-per-use pricing model, and automatic scalability. It enables developers to build highly scalable and cost-effective applications that can handle millions of requests without the need for server provisioning or management. AWS Serverless empowers developers to focus on application logic and innovation, accelerating the development process and enabling faster time to market. By leveraging AWS Serverless services, developers can build scalable, resilient, and cost-efficient applications that scale seamlessly and adapt to changing workloads.', 0, 35, 'AWS Serverless Quiz with W3School', 'FREE', 2, 'http://localhost:8763/api/v1/files/images/exams/15d4b778-0189-1000-b223-9a42aa7808f8.jpg', '2023-07-02 16:00:09.472808', '2');
